ARTIFACT-GROUNDED SCORING RULES:
For each dimension, you MUST reference specific artifacts from the pipeline output.
Generic assessments are rejected. State the specific evidence for every score you give.

DIMENSION 1 — Requirement coverage (0-20)
Count how many requirements from missing_requirements were addressed by specific components in architecture_design.
20: All identified requirements have a traceable component
15: >80% of requirements have a traceable component
10: 50-80% of requirements have a traceable component
5:  <50% of requirements have a traceable component
0:  No traceability between requirements and components
State: "N of M requirements are traceable to components"

DIMENSION 2 — Characteristic alignment (0-20)
For each characteristic with measurable_target, check if the architecture design explicitly addresses it.
20: All primary characteristics have dedicated components
15: >75% of primary characteristics are addressed
10: 50-75% addressed, including the top-ranked one
5:  Only the top-ranked characteristic is addressed
0:  Architecture style does not serve primary characteristics
State: "N of M primary characteristics have dedicated design"

DIMENSION 3 — Trade-off quality (0-20)
Count trade-offs in trade_offs list. Check each has a specific rationale, names what was sacrificed, and references a characteristic.
20: Every component or style decision has a documented trade-off with specific sacrifice and rationale
15: Most decisions have trade-offs, some are generic
10: Trade-offs exist but are generic and context-free
5:  Fewer than 3 trade-offs total
0:  No trade-off documentation
State: "N trade-offs documented, N with specific rationale"

DIMENSION 4 — ADL enforceability (0-20)
Count ADL blocks in adl_blocks. Check each has a non-empty REQUIRES field and a PROMPT field >= 50 characters.
20: N >= 5 ADL blocks, all with testable ASSERT conditions
15: N = 3-4 ADL blocks, all enforceable
10: N = 2 ADL blocks or some are vague
5:  N = 1 ADL block
0:  No ADL blocks generated
State: "N ADL blocks, N with specific enforcement tooling"

DIMENSION 5 — Risk awareness (0-20)
Use fmea_risks list. Count risks by RPN and degradation type.
20: >=6 FMEA risks identified, >=2 with RPN>100 and mitigations specified, degradation types classified
15: 4-5 risks with mitigations
10: 2-3 risks identified, mitigations generic or absent
5:  1-2 risks identified
0:  No FMEA risks
State: "N FMEA risks, N critical (RPN>100), N with mitigations"

DIMENSION 6 — Cross-section consistency (0-10 bonus)
Check whether buy-vs-build decisions are honoured in the architecture design.
For each BUY or ADOPT decision in buy_vs_build_analysis:
If the component appears as "external" in architecture_design: +2 points (max 10)
If the component appears as an internal service despite a buy/adopt recommendation: -2 points
State: "N of M buy/adopt decisions reflected as external components"

IMPORTANT: Calculate the score from the actual counts above.
Do not estimate. The score MUST match the counts you state.

Also determine improvement recommendations and whether re-iteration is needed.
Re-iteration is recommended when the total score is below 60 OR when any single dimension scores below 10.

